
<title>Prestige</title>



<div id="header">
<h1 class="title">Prestige</h1>
</div>


<ul>
<li>Graphs outcomevspredictor variables holding the rest constant (also called partial-regression plots)</li>
</ul>
<pre class="r"><code>library(car)
reg1 &lt;-lm(prestige ~ education + income + type, data = Prestige)
avPlots(reg1, id.n=2, id.cex=0.7)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-1" alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-1" width="672" /></p>
<pre class="r"><code># Help identify the effect(or influence) of an observation on the regression coefficient of the predictor variable</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>library(car)
reg1 &lt;-lm(prestige ~ education + income + type, data = Prestige)
influenceIndexPlot(reg1, id.n=3)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-2" alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-2" width="672" /></p>
<ul>
<li><p>Cook’s distance measures how much an observation influences the overall model or predicted values</p></li>
<li><p>Studentizidedresiduals are the residuals divided by their estimated standard deviation as a way to standardized</p></li>
<li><p>Bonferronitest to identify outliers</p></li>
<li><p>Hat-points identify influential observations (have a high impact on the predictor variables)</p></li>
</ul>
<p>NOTE: If an observation is an outlier and influential (high leverage) then that observation can change the fit of the linear model, it is advisable to remove it. To remove a case(s) type</p>
<pre class="r"><code># reg1a &lt;-update(prestige.reg4, subset=rownames(Prestige) != &quot;general.managers&quot;)
#reg1b &lt;-update(prestige.reg4, subset= !(rownames(Prestige) %in% c(&quot;general.managers&quot;,&quot;medical.technicians&quot;)))</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>library(car)
reg1 &lt;-lm(prestige ~ education + income + type, data = Prestige)
influencePlot(reg1, id.n=3)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-4" alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-4" width="672" /></p>
<pre><code>##                            StudRes     Hat   CookD
## general.managers          -1.31346 0.33504 0.41534
## lawyers                   -0.08277 0.10360 0.01265
## physicians                -0.39532 0.22420 0.09548
## medical.technicians        2.82109 0.06859 0.33023
## service.station.attendant -2.21884 0.05971 0.24494
## electronic.workers         2.22519 0.02701 0.16240</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code># Creates a bubble-plot combining the display of Studentizedresiduals, hat-values, and Cook's distance (represented in the circles).</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>library(car)
reg1 &lt;-lm(prestige ~ education + income + type, data = Prestige)
qqPlot(reg1)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-5" alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-5" width="672" /></p>
<pre class="r"><code># Look for the tails, points should be close to the line or within the confidence intervals.</code></pre>
